description: From Middle English misreporten, equivalent to mis- +‎ report.

verbs.description: misreport (third-person singular simple present misreports, present participle misreporting, simple past and past participle misreported)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To report erroneously; to give an incorrect account of.
examples: Often, she would discover facts that had been overlooked or misreported by the mainstream press.

description: From Middle English mysreport, equivalent to mis- +‎ report.
